PY  - 1984
Y1  - 1984/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297709
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 51
IS  - 1
SP  - 129
EP  - 138
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - When government liabilities (including money) are held in private portfolios only as stores of value and do not provide additional services (such as liquidity), real variables are not affected by changes in the money supply due to the government's trading in real assets (open market operations). This neutrality of monetary policy fails if the government either trades in nominal assets, or it distributes subsidies and levies taxes.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297709
ER  - 



